Detectives have shot and killed four robbery with violence suspects in shootout along Juja Road in Nairobi and recovered two loaded pistols and four knives. According to the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI), the gang of six had Sunday morning robbed two residents of White Castle and attempted to get away with their car. “On receiving the report from the victims, detectives based [at] Pangani Police Station launched a manhunt and caught up with the gang of six, who disobeyed orders to surrender and engaged in a gun fight,” DCI said in a tweet Sunday morning. DCI added that two suspects managed to escape toward Kosovo during the shootout. The detectives have launched a manhunt for the two.  